Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from your #fridge{} to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Peel the @garlic cloves{3}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the potatoes and garlic to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any large ones.

Pop the broccoli florets onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the edges are crispy and slightly charred, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

> If you'd prefer to boil your broccoli, boil it in step 4 while the sauce simmers for 3-5 mins, until tender.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{5%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

While the steak is resting, heat a drizzle of oil in the (now empty) frying pan on medium heat.

Add the shallot and stir until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, then add the @cracked black pepper{1%sachet}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water for the sauce{100%ml} and allow it to reduce by about half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce the heat, then stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g} and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{splash}(if you have any) and mash the potatoes and garlic with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

When everything's ready, slice the steaks.

Share the steaks, mashed potatoes and broccoli between your plates.

Pour your peppercorn sauce over the steaks to finish.

Enjoy!